---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Aircraft Squad Building" 
  description="Aircraft squad building guide for Last War: Survival."
>
  <h1>Aircraft Squad Building</h1>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p>Aircraft is a strong counter to many Tank compositions and excels at burst damage and mobility. It is often the second squad type players build after establishing a solid Tank foundation.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Hero Focus Order (Mid-Game Guidance)</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">Exact order can shift by season and server meta. Prioritize your highest-starred heroes while following general community consensus for efficient progression.</p>

  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Priority</th>
          <th>Hero</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold text-[#f59e0b]">1</td>
          <td><strong>DVA</strong></td>
          <td>Often the highest priority Aircraft DPS. Push stars and exclusive weapon early.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">2</td>
          <td><strong>Carlie</strong></td>
          <td>Excellent frontline tank for Aircraft squads. Strong durability and utility.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">3</td>
          <td><strong>Schuyler</strong></td>
          <td>High damage backline carry. Frequently prioritized in Aircraft builds.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">4</td>
          <td><strong>Morrison / Lucius</strong></td>
          <td>Solid support options that provide buffs or secondary damage.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="font-bold">5</td>
          <td><strong>Flex (e.g. Fiona, Marshall variants)</strong></td>
          <td>Use your best available starred hero that fits the formation.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Positioning Notes</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">Aircraft formations often differ from Tank. Typical strong setups emphasize protecting key backline damage dealers while using mobile or high-HP units to draw fire. Test in-game and adjust based on your server's common matchups.</p>

  <h2>Skill &amp; Progression Priority</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Focus active skills on your main DPS (often DVA or Schuyler) first.</li>
    <li>Build Carlie’s tanking and utility skills early.</li>
    <li>Star and gear your core 3–4 heroes before spreading resources.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Visual Guides</h2>
  <p class="text-sm">Excellent Aircraft squad guides following the same format (hero headshots in priority order + skill/star priorities) are available from community creators.</p>

  <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-[#1a253f] border border-[#f59e0b]/30 rounded">
    <p class="text-sm"><strong>Support Aethernis’ work:</strong> <a href="https://ko-fi.com/aethernis" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-[#f59e0b]">ko-fi.com/aethernis</a></p>
    <p class="text-xs text-[#8a96b0] mt-1">Search for “Aethernis Aircraft squad guide” on Reddit for high-quality visual references.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6">
    <a href="/squad-building" class="text-[#f59e0b]">← Back to Squad Building Principles</a>
  </div>
</Layout>